lead_paragraph: Russell Westbrook had 13 points, 14 rebounds and 12 assists to become the first player with 17 triple-doubles in a season in 27 years, and the Oklahoma City Thunder routed the Denver Nuggets 124-102 on Tuesday night.

headline.print_headline: Westbrook's 17th Triple-Double Leads Thunder Over Nuggets
